<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 1:56AM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF SOUTHWESTERN DIVIDE
COUNTY THROUGH 230 AM CDT...
At 156 AM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 5 miles east of
Writing Rock State Historical Site, or 21 miles southwest of Crosby,
moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Divide
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
